<br>
Okay, today I log on about 6:30 CST to see my guild prepping to step up and clear to saryrn, our first attempt. We meet at zone, have 52 people. Average raid force for us.<br>
<br>
It took us 6 solid hours to clear to Saryrn. SIX hours. Guess what loot we got? ONE melee belt that didn't even have 100 @#%$ hps. Oh, did I mention two eth parchments that our raid leader probably destroyed because he was so pissed?<br>
<br>
That's right... no runes, no specs, no decent loot.<br>
<br>
We killed names with AE rampage and a max hit of 3.5k. And the corpses rotted in 30 seconds.<br>
<br>
We cleared for 6 damn hours. And nothing.<br>
<br>
It's just as bad in any PoP zone.<br>
<br>
I'd write a rant about this but it's 1:30... all I can say is:<br>
<br>
Make mininameds (or difficult ones, anyways -- IE Torment, Decay, etc) drop a GUARANTEED armor mold or rare loot as well as a guaranteed spec or rune. Please.<br>
<br>
Elemental planes seem to be okay, but damn, fix the tier 2 plane crap. Tactics is about the only one where mininameds are worth doing and half the time their loot sucks too. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=361567">Draogan</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> -- 62 Archmage<br>
